    "This required ~100 days of constant training, with an estimated cost of ~$100 million USD.",
    "Another reason for the rise of AI is the growth of the internet, which enabled large datasetsincluding words, images, audio, and videoto be amassed, annotated, and made available to train AI systems [30].",
    "These datasets can be directly and indirectly used for many AI training purposes.",
    "For example, models used to identify genetic changes by assessing the faces of people with genetic conditions were built on top of (through something called \"transfer learning\") models that leverage vast general databases of facial images [23].Lastly, powerful and popular \"generative AI\" methods involve AI that is used to make (generate) something, such as words, still or video images, sounds, or some combination of these.",
    "Generative AI involves different types of deep learning."
